properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 18 at 12:43AM EST until January 18 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast to east winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts to near 35
kt and seas 5 to 7 feet expected well offshore. Conditions
should gradually improve on Saturday. However, it is possible
that the advisory might need to be extended through Saturday
with upcoming updates.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from East Cape Sable to Chokoloskee FL
out 20 NM, Coastal waters from Chokoloskee to Bonita Beach FL
out 20 NM and Waters from Chokoloskee to Bonita Beach FL from
20 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM EST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

A sudden onset of rough seas may cause hazardous conditions,
which may occur suddenly at jetties and inlets. These conditions
could catch boaters by surprise. Boaters should use caution when
entering or exiting the inlets and jetty areas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST THIS MORNING
